Action Group was the name given to a small group of Justice and Peace volunteers in Aintree North Liverpool in April 1963.
They founded a local community action group to campaign for Heating and Welfare benefits for the elderly in the area. They later included Third World campaigning and Peace working in the scope of their concerns.

The name originated from three study groups looking at local issues, by working to the Cardijn principles of SEE, JUDGE and ACT.

The Action Group was the the working title given to the third group who were to act on the findings of the first two principles.
They are still in operation as a registered charity.